cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as automatic speech recognition and word embeddings. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new algorithm for encoding categorical features and output classes. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with machine learning techniques for natural language processing. It may also fall under cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with automatic speech recognition, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a new algorithm for neural network compression.
